You're gonna have to. And there's something else. Something really important. You're gonna have to tell him that I don't love him anymore. That it was all a big mistake....
What?
That I'm never coming back. Ever. So there's no point coming after me....
Please Mum... look I can't....
Yes. You can. Cos it's the only way I'm ever gonna really set him free. Understand?
Aaahh!! It's too hot you silly cow! You're waxing me leg not basting a bleeding turkey.
Sorry about that madam.
You sure you've done this before?
Yes. Loads of times.
How's that Mrs Harris? More comfortable?
Yes thanks. You're not gonna hurt me, are ya?
It might stink a little bit.
First you try and burn me. Then you flay me alive. I'm out of here.
I'm so sorry Mo...
Give me childbirth any day of the week.
You see Mrs Harris? It can be almost painless if it's ‚professionally' done.
Yeah... Well.. I think i'll have the rest off... But keep that torturing psycho out my way.
I think I've seen enough. Leave them to it shall we, Clare?
So do you reckon the little darlings are gonna be impressed then?
They're gonna love it.
Couldn't have done it without you Rox. Thanks.
Pleasure is all mine. Listen you gotta keep slippery eel Beale in his place in't you.
Mission accomplished.
Where is Ian anyway? he should have the food laid out by now?
Thanks. I won't you let you down.
I couldn't give it to Clare could I?
Just forgot my scarf.
See you tomorrow then Tanya.
D'you want me to get that for you?
No it's okay, It's fine...
I've done reception work before.
yes... if you don't mind. Could you take a message, tell 'em I'll call them back. Thank you.

Good afternoon Booty. Yep, just one moment Mrs Finlay. I'll just check for you. Mrs George? If you'd like to take a seat someone will be with you shortly. Sorry to keep you waiting. We can offer you 11.30 or 2.30. Whichever's better for you. That's fine. Ok, that's in the diary. Any problems, give us a call. Look forward to seeing you then.
Where the hell's Ian? We need the food. Now!
Sorry. We've been really busy. I haven't made half of it yet.
He got you to do it? Cheeky git!
Oi! I heard that!
Good! This was your job. Not hers!
It was just a few sausages on sticks....
If it was that simple you should've got it all sorted before getting drunk with your lardy di da mates down the Town Hall.
I was networking. Getting us contacts. And I am not drunk. I met a lovely fella, Councillor Tunstall, he was very interested..
Never mind interest. How many bookings did you get exactly?
Well... Nothing firm. But at this stage it's all about building relationships....
We're not gonna get very far then are we? Cos you don't get on with anyone.
You gonna let him talk to me like that?
What goes around comes around Ian.
Where you going?
To sort this mess out before we commit professional suicide.
Do you like George, Minty?
Not really, no. I've had enough of this. I'm gonna go and see what's going on.
There they are. Come on up. Told you there was nothing to worry about. George is always right.. ﬁYou've got to have faithﬂ..
Where's Hazel?
I'm not sure.
Wasn't she at the flat?
Yeah but......
Why didn't you bring her here then?
She's.... ...gone.
Gone? What d'you mean gone?
Look I'm sorry mate....
I don't understand....
She's upset about the baby that's all... Her head's all over the place....
No. She's had enough. She's been thinking, she wants out.
She didn't say that,
Look, she thinks it's time to move on. Get a bit more excitement back in her life....
No...no, Hazel wouldn't say that. Not my Hazel.
But she can't just go. What about the wedding?
What's going on Gal? What's going on? I don't understand mate. You said you were gonna go and get her, you promised...
yeah I know but... She don't love you no more!
Hazel! Don't do this please! Talk to me! Please! I love you! I love you.....
I'm sorry mate.
This is nothing to do
I don't.
What?
Congratulations Gal. You've got what you always wanted.
No....you don't understand..
Oh but I do. There's only one person to blame for this mate... And that's you.
Hazel...I'm Hazel, I'm here, hang on babe...

This is Marni Merrick from ﬁTo Love and To Cherishﬂ with a message for our very own happy lovebirds - Minty and Hazel. Maddy is on maternity leave so I'll be handling the competition from now on. Sorry to ring so early but I thought I better remind you about our exciting photo shoot this evening.... No need to worry. It's gonna be lots of fun with plenty of nibbles and champagne to get you in the mood. And fingers crossed you'll soon be enjoying the wedding of your dreams!
Easy Hev. You'll be done for indecent assault.
Just making sure he doesn't catch a chill that's all
Yeah well before you ask. He ain't stopping here.
Where's he supposed to go? Minty hates him now.
It's not my problem.
But it's the photo shoot tonight. We'll have to get Hazel back.
She's probably shacked up with some other mug by now. It's history.
No. Garry might've given up on her. But I haven't. I'm not letting Hazel spoil our big day.
You gotta find her first.
What is it love?
Final demand for my pitch. I can't pay it.
How soon do you need the money?
End of the day. It's a joke.
Well why don't you have a sale...Real knock down prices...That'd buy you some time.
Then what? I've got a stall with nothing to sell. Well done mum.
At least you wouldn't lose it. I could help.
No thanks. I'm alright.
Mo, you'll give Stacey a hand won't you? She's in a terrible fix. She's gotta shift a lot of gear by the end of today otherwise she loses her pitch.
Sorry. I've got plans.
But this is her last chance.
Might be mine n'all. I'll give you a hand tomorrow alright?
I might not have a stall tomorrow. But don't worry, don't put yourself out on my account. Everyone round here knows. I ain't worth it!

Scene_info: BEALES' - LIVING AREA INT DAY LIGHT
Line: Paracetamol's in the kitchen cupboard!

Scene_info: BEALES' - LIVING AREA INT DAY LIGHT
Line: Good morning. Lovely day.

Scene_info: BEALES' - LIVING AREA INT DAY LIGHT
Line: There's a half naked man in our house. I think he's got something to do with your brother!
Hazel. It's Heather. I know you're upset. But I'm sure we can sort it all out if you just come home.... And don't forget it's the photo shoot tonight. I know you won't let us down.
You're wasting your time Heather. My mum don't wanna be found. You ain't gonna find her.
Nice uniform.
At least I've got a job to go to.
Looking forward to your first day?
What do you want?
Just trying to be friendly.
I won.
Fair and square. If you really need a job maybe Dot'll give you some shifts at the launderette. But I wouldn't bother hassling Tanya coz you'll be wasting your time.
Morning girls.
Morning Tanya. Where shall I put my coat?
Gaynor will show you.Clare - Gaynor, Gaynore - Clare.
I thought I got the job?
You did.
So what's Clare doing here?
She really helped me out on reception yesterday. And what with Hazel needing time off, make sense to give her a go.
I'll be back later in case there's any problems. But until then. I'm sure you'll both make her very welcome.
Something smart? You come to the wrong place then. I specialise in trash no one wants to be seen dead in.
What're you playing at?
I'm going under anyway. I thought I might as well have a bit of fun while I'm at it.
No Stacey. I can't let you do this to yourself...
Mum...
She needs to shift this lot by the end of the day...
You really don't have to do this...
I'm supposed to be peeling spuds but as it's you I'm sure I can find someone to cover.
That's settled then. Now...You can do buy one get one free. Three for one. All the shops are doing it.
yes, I know Mum but....
Just give it a try Stacey. Please.
Where's the old Stacey Slater sparkle?
Ian! Concentrate!
Oh no! How can I? My house has been invaded by the Village People.
Don't be ridiculous.
What, you think it's funny do you? It's alright for Christian to bring back whoever he likes. Whenever he likes. It's our house!
Of course not.
I'm glad to hear it! I shouldn't be confronted by some hairy bloke's lunchbox every time I wanna stick the kettle on. What about the kids!
Look, there's no need to shout. I agree with you alright? I'll make sure it doesn't happen again.
Go on then, I want it sorted. Now!
See you then, bye. Gaynor needs someone to sweep up. And I'll have a coffee please. Milk. No sugar.
I'm a beauty consultant. I don't sweep up. And I don't make coffee.
And I say you do.
Since when?
Tanya doesn't pay you to sit around on your...
Look, get over yourself. I ain't your slave. You do it.
Fine. I will. But I'll be having a word with Tanya about your aggressive attitude.
Good morning Booty's.

Cut and colour with Gaynor? One minute. 12 o'clock's no problem at all. In fact you're in luck. Yeah we got a special promotion on today. Everything half price between 12 and 1. I know. So spread the word among your friends. And just tell them to ask for Clare.

Scene_info: BEALES' - LIVING AREA INT DAY LIGHT
Line: Good isn't it?

Scene_info: BEALES' - LIVING AREA INT DAY LIGHT
Line: Didn't know you could do all this?

Scene_info: BEALES' - LIVING AREA INT DAY LIGHT
Line: I'm multi-talented Jane. Ian doesn't know how lucky he is having me as a partner.

Scene_info: BEALES' - LIVING AREA INT DAY LIGHT
Line: yeah well, It's your other partners he's worried about. What the hell were you playing at bringing that bloke back to our house?

Scene_info: BEALES' - LIVING AREA INT DAY LIGHT
Line: Thought Ian might enjoy the sight of Jeph in his boxer shorts. Bring out his repressed tendencies...

Scene_info: BEALES' - LIVING AREA INT DAY LIGHT
Line: You set that up. I knew it.

Scene_info: BEALES' - LIVING AREA INT DAY LIGHT
Line: I couldn't resist it. Did you see the look on his face?

Scene_info: BEALES' - LIVING AREA INT DAY LIGHT
Line: This is serious Christian. I'm just as angry as he is. And before you say anything I'd feel exactly the same if it was a woman.

Scene_info: BEALES' - LIVING AREA INT DAY LIGHT
Line: Come off it Jane. It was just a wind up. Nothing happened if that's what you're worried about.

Scene_info: BEALES' - LIVING AREA INT DAY LIGHT
Line: Show some respect. This is our family home. Do it again and you're out.

Scene_info: BEALES' - LIVING AREA INT DAY LIGHT
Line: Ok, ok...I'll be a good boy in future. I promise.

Was it definitely 12 o' clock? I'm really sorry about this... there seems to be some kind of mix up...Excuse me a moment... I've got a regular claiming I booked her in with Gaynor this morning and that I offered all of her friends a 50% discount. Do you know anything about it?
No.
Look, Tanya's gonna be back in a minute. I need you to stay here and help me sort out this mess.
Sorry. I've got plans.
You don't wanna make an enemy out of me Chelsea.
Oh dear...I'm so scared...
Come on ladies. Take a look! Everything 50% off! And if you don't like the discount - make me an offer.
Right, who's next?
That's a fiver darlin'. They're two for fifteen quid. You don't get that down the High Street.
Oh Nan, Halloween's in October you know!
Cheeky mare!
Oh hello, I was just coming to find you. How's everything going, alright?
I think Clare might be a bit out of her depth to be honest with you. She's like struggling with the booking system. And clients are getting a bit upset.
Oh...right. Thanks for telling me.
Hazel...Pick up... Please baby'...
Thought you might be hungry. Made an extra round.
Ta Heather. That's very kind.
No Minty then.
Nah... And if you don't mind like, I'm a bit busy..
Don't suppose you've heard from your mum..
You might as well call the magazine. Cancel the whole thing. It ain't never gonna happen.
But we can't let our dreams of being Best Man and Bridesmaid fade into the sunset?
It was never my dream Heather. I just want my mate back. Now if you'll excuse me....
Yeah... Course...
Have a nice long lunch did you?
Well...
Only Clare was telling me how she'd asked you to help her sort things out.
yeah well, I'd made arrangements....
Well next time I'd put the Salon before a gossipy chat with your mates or you won't have a job to come back to.
Yes Tanya.
And for your information - far from messing things up this morning - Clare has done a fantastic job.

In fact I'm so impressed I'm making her my assistant manager. So I suggest you show her a little bit more respect from now on. And it seems to me a little bit of team building is in order, so we're gonna stay and have a meeting after work. And if things don't improve after that I'll be forced to think again. Do you understand Chelsea?
yep.
I think you owe me an apology.
Oh yeah. Look, I'm sorry for using the last of the coffee. I'll get some more while I'm out.
That's me done. Sold my last thong.
Oh Thank you. I couldn't have done it without you.
So where you taking me then?
Might stretch to a drink in the Vic. This has gotta cover next month.
Must've made more than that?
No. I owed a lot of back rent n'all. This just takes me back to square one.
Steven! Family meeting. Now.
Looks like you might be needing that drink. See you later.
This had better be important. Coz I'm meeting Lauren.
Jane see you come over?
Don't think so.
Good. Because the time has come for me to take matters into my own hands.
What are you on about?
Christian.
What's he supposed to have done?
Well..we're all aware that ...he's... different....
Different from what?
From me for instance....Well he's of a different...
You don't like him because he's gay.
Now I never said that.
You didn't have to.
It doesn't matter what he is. It's who he's bringing back here. And what they're doing?
Why? What've they been doing?
Use your imagination Peter!
I'm with Dad. Why should I have to queue up for the shower with some bloke I've never met before?
It's not like you have to get in with him!
Yeah but do we really want strange men hanging around the house? They could be anyone.
My point exactly. Peter?
I think he's alright. But if he's bringing weirdos back....
This is so unfair! it's only one guy. And he was actually really nice .
You spoke to him?
Made me a cup of tea. Didn't seem like a serial killer.
Well. I think we should have a vote on this. All those in favour of Christian turning our home into a love hotel raise your hand. You look a bit ﬁundecidedﬂ there Peter.
Sure you don't want Bobby here. You might need his vote.
All those against.
That new game you wanted comes out Friday, doesn't it? Motion carried.
Minty? Got your message. Finished up early.
Funny how your sad little life fits into two bin bags.
No... Don't do this. Please.
I think we're finished here. So why don't you just pick up your rubbish and go.
We can sort this out. We're best mates.
Not anymore we're not.
You can't pin all this on me. I'm theone caught in the middle.

Hazel was fine when I left her. We had a cuddle. We even had a little chat about what we were gonna have for tea. Then a few hours later she's in a taxi speeding out of my life for good. And who was the last person to see her? You!
You know what? You want the honest truth? I was only trying to protect you.

I don't need protecting thanks. I'm big enough and ugly enough to look after myself. And that's what I intend to do in the future. So, no more Garry and Minty. No more ﬁbest matesﬂ. I will never forgive you for this.
Oh come on.
Oh come on, Mint...
Have a nice life! Keys.
Had a good day by the looks of it.
What's it to you?
Couldn't help noticing you've shifted most of your stock. Might be able to do you a favour.
Got my own suppliers thanks.
I wouldn't be bothering you. But I've just picked up a load of bankrupt stock. You'd really like it. All fantastic quality. It'll fly off your stall in a day.
I've heard that before.
I can see you're not interested. Sorry for wasting your time.
Hold on. Maybe I should have a look. See if it's as good as you say it is.
I could bring the van round now if you like. No pressure.
Alright.
You won't regret it.
What do you want?
I'm prepared to start again if you are.
Is this a wind up?
Look, neither of us are gonna last very long if we can't we be friends.
You wanna be my friend? Alright. You can get your hands dirty for a change. You can clean the sinks. Take the rubbish out. I'll be downstairs with my feet up till Tanya gets back.
OK. If that's what it takes.
Thought we'd got rid of you.
Yeah... I'm sorry... Look I tried Gus but he ain't back yet... Please Shirl, I'm just knackered carrying these around all day.
Well don't plan on stopping long. I like my home to be a man free zone unless I've got use for him. And I don't think you quite fit that category.
Pay no attention. You can always share my room.
Come on. Let's get this lot cleared up. I'll
She's always been trouble Hev. All me life.
No... Don't say that.
It's true. I should never have listened to her.
What d'you mean?
Doesn't matter.
No... A problem shared is a problem halved. Get it off your chest and you'll feel much better.
I thought I was doing the right thing....
I'm sure you were. Whatever it was.
No. Mum asked me to lie Hev. To paint her as a villain so Minty wouldn't blame himself. Trouble is he blames me. Thinks I put her up to it.
So she still loves him?
In her own twisted way.
Minty'll come round. And in the mean time..I'm here.
Yeah well, we've had worse times I suppose...think this is the end of the road though. No more Friday night Vindaloos... no more Saturday football... no more nights in watching Top Gear on DVD...
I like Top Gear.
Minty's the kindest, most generous bloke you could ever meet. And I've just gone and blown it. Thanks mum.
If Hazel still loves him odds are she'll come walking back in any
You're still going on about that flaming competition. I'm breaking my heart here.
Just trying to keep positive Garry. Heather Trott never gives up hope.
Thanks Mum.
What for?
Getting me out of trouble.
You just needed a push, that's all. What did the market inspector say?
He said he doesn't need the money till Friday. he seems impressed I'm getting myself together.
You need a bit of luck after the year you've had. Things can only get better eh?
You wouldn't believe how much I paid for this bra. And not so much as a sneaky grope.
I knew you was up to something. Who was it?
Fat Elvis.
You must be blind or desperate.
Stacey.....
No it's alright for her to have a go. I'm getting too old for this game. Time to hang up me fluffy hand cuffs for good.
Never thought I'd hear you swear off blokes. I still think you're gorgeous. Even if you did pick a walking beer gut over me.....
Sorry Stace... But I thought I was on a promise.
I'll go and get you a drink. Celebrate your new life as a Nun.
Right, I can't stay long coz I've left the girls on their own. Oscar's just gone off in the pram so far so good.
Right, well we've had a chat and we're really sorry. Aren't we Chelsea?
Sorry's not good enough. I need to know that this kind of thing won't happen again. Got enough childish behaviour to cope with at home.
It won't. I promise.
Chelsea?
It won't.
Good. Right, well let's celebrate, shall we. I've got a bottle of white in the fridge up here. Chelsea. Do us a favour and get us some glasses out back, will ya. Didn't take you long did it?
I'm not a thief if that's what you're thinking......
Should've trusted my instincts in the first place. Just get out of here before I call the police.
Look, Tanya. It's my fault.
yeah...
I should've talked to you first. I'm really sorry.
No. It's me that should be apologising. I'm so sorry Chelsea. Look, you have them on me darlin'. I should never have jumped to conclusions like that.
It's alright, thanks.
Got that blokes phone number. Seeing him next week.
Thought you was jacking it all in.
Changed me mind. There's life in the old dog yet Stace. It's no good. Gotta get these lace undies off. They're splitting me difference.
Nan, that's too much information.
Can I get anyone a drink? Celebrate our little deal?
Yeah, same again thanks. Mum, this is Roger. The bloke who sold me the gear.
Oh...Pleased to meet you...
Likewise. Your daughter's got a keen eye for business Mrs Slater.
Oh yes...My Stacey's always had a good head on her shoulders.
What can I get you?
Two white wines. And a scotch please love.
Just excuse me a minute, please.
Oi! You're supposed to be working!
Phil I have to take this. It's Two whites wine and a scotch. Bloke with the tie.
What you doing talking to her? She's family.
Stacey? Just done a bit of business as it happens.
It better be kosher or you're dead mate.
It's all bankrupt stock. Got all the paperwork and everything.
Funny that. Coz everything else you sell is knocked off.
£7.60 please.
First time for everything Mo.
Mid day? yeah I'll be there.
Shirley? Everything alright? Oi! What're you doing?
It's my boy. Dean. He's coming home.
Hazel...stop this now...we know you still love him really....so come home please... Garry's really upset ... And the magazine's gonna be here any minute... We're all counting on you.
Oi! What the hell was all that about?
Simple. I put them there. Planned the whole thing.
Why would you do something like that?
because I wanted to show you who's boss. To prevent any further ‚misunderstandings'.
You evil cow! Well I'm gonna go and tell Tanya what you're really like. And thenmaybe, she can throw you back in the gutter where you belong!
Be my guest. But who do you think she's gonna believe? Me? Or some lying ex con she never wanted back in the first place. You better start behaving yourself Chelsea.
Cos now you know I can break you any time I want.
Let me in. Please. It's freezing out here.
Yeah I know.It's a mess innit. But you know what? I like it. And if you've come here with some pathetic sob story from Garry, you can just do one.
But there's more to it Minty. You don't understand...
Oh here we go. Garry, clear off! And take your messenger with you!
Minty? It's Marni. From the magazine.
Can you let us in? We've got an awful lot to get through this evening.
Let them in. There's still a chance Hazel might come back. Just keep them talking.
Can you let us in? I tried to call. Several times. Didn't you get my messages? Have you been burgled or something?
Some kids broke in. Made a bit of a mess.
How dreadful....
Look I think you might've had a bit of a wasted journey.....
Don't worry. It doesn't have to be here. We can use a bar or a hotel lounge or something. But we do need to get hair and make-up underway.... Where is the lovely Hazel?
Look I'm really sorry, but there's....
So sorry to keep you all waiting. But that is the Bride's prerogative after all! I'm Hazel. Hazel Hobbs. Very pleased to meet you.
Morning. What are you doing? That's my stuff.
I thought I'd save you the trouble of carrying it down the stairs.
Oi, what you doing?
You better hurry up before they take that away as rubbish. Come on shift yourself, I've gotta get this place ready for Dean.
Look Shirley, you can't do this alright? I've got no place to live.
There you go, confusing me with somebody who gives a toss. This isn't a homeless hostel, and you are not my problem. Now get.
He could've waited til I got up. Said goodbye. It's cos of me, ain't it? I messed it all up.
No you ain't -
It's the same as with Minty. I spoil everything - I thought he was gonna to explode when I said I was Hazel.
He went through with it though didn't he - had his picture taken with ya.
Yeah, chucked me out afterwards, as soon as she left, told me to stop interfering - oh, that's gorgeous. Thanks. You not having any?
This all the only breakfast I need.
I should take up smoking. I might lose a bit of weight.
Oh what and get lung cancer in return - smart move Hev - ain't you got enough problems as it is.
Ah, you're always looking out for me, ain't you Shirl? You're my best mate, d'you know that?
Yes. I want you to move out.
I'd keep out of your way. I could just kip on the sofa, I wouldn't mind.
Say if Dean wanted to chill out with a lager, watching late night tv? How's that gonna work?
Don't send me back to my Mum's Shirl.
I'm not. Look don't worry, I've got it all worked out. It's just temporary. Dean ain't gonna want to live with his Mum for long either but while he does, I wanna be there for him.
Yes, but why do I have to go -
Oh you know why Hev. This is my second chance. To be the Mum he's always wanted me to be. And he's gonna need me even more now Kevin's gone.
Well, now I feel really selfish.
No. You're gold, you are. Thanks Hev. I knew you'd understand. Come on, I'll help you pack.
What, he's your brother in law - so don't try and dump him on me - 'cause he ain't my responsibility.
You're not homophobic, are you Phil? Cos you know what they say don't ya? That just means you're a little bit Dorothy yourself.
One day Beale, I'm going to beat you to death. You want to make it today, that's fine by me alright.
Maybe that's why he's so angry, he's repressed.
Right, that's it.
I'm messing, I'm messing.
Alright, okay, enough. Alright? Just pack it in. Christian went because Ian didn't want him there. Because he's scared of him too.
No, I'm not. He kept bringing blokes back to the house. I don't want a naked stranger in my kitchen.
Well, exactly.
Yah.
He wasn't naked.
Might as well have been. Peter's at an impressionable age.
Well, exactly. That's my thinking with Ben. It's puberty, isn't it? I mean they're all confused.
Being gay isn't contagious.
She don't understand.
Well he ain't staying in the Vic.
Yeah. He's not staying at our house either alright. He'll
Because it ain't our problem.
You sure you don't mind?
We.ll be alright. Say bye bye Mummy.
Right then well look. I've only just fed and changed him so he should be alright. But there's a bottle made up in the fridge if he does need it. And um, well, I'll only be a couple of hours.
Take your time, go shopping, treat yourself.
No, I'll be right back.
You're gonna get a raise, you carry on like this. Bye bye darling.
Help yourself to tea and coffee won't ya?
Thanks.
Well, I've got my mobile.
Here we are.
I'm really sorry you're homeless Heather, but you ain't staying here alright?
You got two spare rooms, why not? It doesn't make sense. How are you two going to win this wedding competition if don't even look like a couple?
I ain't doing the competition anymore. I told you that last night. Didn't I?
You tell the magazine people?
Not yet no. 'Cause I didn't want to get her into trouble for impersonating somebody else.
As far as they're still concerned, she's still Hazel.
Yeah. Until I phone them, tell 'em we've had a row. And tell 'em it's all off. Oi.
Don't you wanna find out why she did it first? Tell him. And listen this time cos she was trying to help you.
Well I...
Hazel told Garry to make her look like the villain so you didn't have to blame yourself. That means she still cares about you Minty.
She still loves you, Minty.
That's why Heather carried on with this competition. She knows there's still something between you two.
You can't give up on her yet. Not while there's still a chance.
She still loves me?
Of course. Why wouldn't she? She just doesn't think she's worth it, that's all. You've got to prove to her that she is.
How?
By going and finding her again. It's your destiny Minty. Even Garry knows that.
That's your first port of call - make things right. Go and find him and ask him if he knows how she feels and if he can find her again. Cos if he don't know...
No one knows. Yeah. Oh what have I done? He was trying to be a mate weren't he, all he was trying to do was help...
Then go and make things better before it's too late.
Yeah. She really still loves me. I knew she still loved me. I never doubted it really. I've gotta go and find Garry.
I told ya I'd find ya a place to stay.
He said I couldn't move in.

Okay. So who the hell was that?
Tell me again why I'm here?
I'm proving a point. Soon as they crank out a slow number Heather's gonna be over me like a shot, wanting to smooch with the Hobbster. It's not working, is it?
It's too noisy in here to sort it out. Here.
This is a great idea. Celebrate me moving in - thanks Garry.
Do you fancy him or what?
Eh? No. no.
Well, she ain't going to admit it, is she?
No, no, really, I don't. Honest.
So why do you wanna move in so badly eh? Why do you wanna win that competition?
Cos we're gonna share the prize money. Means I can have cosmetic surgery. You know, liposuction, nose job, the lot.
I'm gonna look beautiful. Come on, let's dance.
There you are, why's she having all that done eh? So I'll go out with her, that's why.
Jack wants her to leave but she won't go. I need you to help me.
She looks alright to me.
She's off her face.
Well, let's try and catch up then. Have as much as fun as she is.

I like Jane, well I love her, but it's, it's not a ‚Great' love. You know? Like when you want someone with every fiber of your being, and I've had that. I, I know what it's like and well with Jane... I wish I could. I really do.
That's a dilemma, isn't it? Do you stay with someone comfortable, tolerable or do you search for what your heart really desires.
Exactly.
Ian.
Mmm.
You deserve better.
I know.
You shouldn't deny yourself or let others hold you back from what you really want.

Absolutely. That is, that is it, that is what I've done, my whole life. I have been held back. I, I, I could have gone to the Palace. I could have been meeting with the Queen. And I could of picked up awards, I could have done all of that.
And still could.
Oh, wouldn't that be something. If my Dad had known his son would meet the Queen...
Ian. Will you be my guest at the Palace? Will you come with me and meet the Queen.
I'd like nothing better.
I don't think Jack's coming out of his office, anytime soon. Sorry about that.
I haven't been great company, have I?
It's alright. I wasn't expecting anything. Apart from a friendly face. Dot said you were looking for some mates.
Yeah, I was. Gus, look I'm sorry. It's just...I'm just getting over someone, a bit wounded, that's all.
Don't worry about it, it's Dot I was doing a favour for anyway, not you. But let me know when you're ready to go eh and I'll walk you back, make sure you're safe.
Gus? I'm ready now. Thank
There's no need for you to stand and watch. No reason I can think of.
There's no reason for you to be checking the books - it's Friday night.
Mm. Sounds like you didn't expect it, which makes it exactly the right time. You see it's all a matter of trust isn't it?
Fine. When you've decided you've been punished enough, you let me know, okay?
Stacey... Stacey, can you hear me?
If you could stepback sir.
I'm not stepping anywhere.
Can you tell me exactly what happened.
I dunno... One minute she's sitting there , having a few drinks, next minute she's on the floor...
Did she take anything?
No.
Are you sure? Only we need to be clear on this.
Why's she staring at me like that?
Sir.
Look at her eyes look like they're made of glass. C'mon that's not right.
Sir, did she take anything?
---No! She didn't! Now stop her staring at me like that. Stacey. Stace... Where are you taking her?
Sir can you just stay here.
Gotcha.

Line: Just get her right, can you do that?
Sweetheart...
What you doing?
I'm Celebrating.
Divorce hearing?
Yeah it's the first one. It's on Valentine's Day. But this year Cupid's going to take his arrows back...
So - it's all over then?
There's no other way to go Lauren. What your Dad did to me, us, there's no coming back from that.
So that's it then? All over?
It's more of a new start. That's how I'm looking at it.
Remember that Valentine's card?That big one dad got you that time? Was so big I could just about hide inside it.
Lauren...
Yeah?
Long time ago now eh?
Is she awake?
Not yet. But she's stable.
Well get back in there and do your job.
If she took something, which I am almost certain of, it would help if I knew what.
She didn't take anything.
I see. Is there any other family member I could contact?
No.
No?
I'm all she needs.
Alright, alright.
Who is it?
Not there yet am I. Hello? Hello? Sorry? Stacey? Uh... Hang on a minute. Is she back yet Stacey?
No idea. Who is it?
Who is it?
Steven Beale.
What's he want this time of night?
What? When??
What's the matter?
He says she collapsed, went off in an ambulance.
Gimme that. What ambulance? What you talking about?
What you doing up?
Heard music.
It was mum. Dancing.
Dancing?
Yeah.
Why?
To celebrate.
We had some good news?
Not exactly.
Why was she celebrating then?
I think it's over Abs... Mum and dad, they're finished.
They can't be.
She got a letter through for the divorce hearing. It's all going ahead.
They can't do that. I won't let them.
Face it Abs. It's too late That evil cow Stacey's ruined everything.
C'mon! You stupid thing.... What? You got a problem eh?
DAD.
Sorry... I Sean...
What are you lot doing here?
What d'you think?
We heard Stacey was hurt.
That's one way of putting it.
What is it, what's happened to her??
Dunno.
Sean, stop messing about tell me you were obviously there, tell me. Please.
I don't know.
You didn't even think to call me?
What you gonna do? You a doctor?
That's my little girl. Where is she? I need to see her.
You can't.
I'm her mum, of course I can see her. She needs me.
To do what? Dribble all over her?
I've brought her clothes and things, I couldn't get grapes, not this time of night---
---Grapes!? Just do us a favour stay out of it eh mum.
I've got to see her, where's the doctor? What's his name? Maybe I know him. I couldn't bear it if anything happens to her.
For once in your useless life will you just pull yourself together. Last thing Stacey needs is you carrying on in it?
Look, let's just sit tight for now eh.
What exactly happened Sean?
I don't know Charlie we were in the club and she just keeled over.
People just don't keel over.
This is awful, I can't bear it, I can't.
Was she on something?
Look I don't know how many other ways I can say it Mo I don't know?
What'd you give her? Ecstasy was it?
Have you got ears Charlie?!
How could you. You promised me you'd look after her, swore to me.
Back off, you ain't helping!
Look at him, guilty as sin. That's why we weren't told. Cos you knew we'd suss you.
You know what if
Max?
Was he there too?
Use your head will you! If she did take something it's cos he pushed her to do it.
That lets you off nice and easy.
You know what I'm out of here.
What? No,you don't, I need you. I'm scared Sean...
You're always scared. I want to know the minute you hear something. Think you can do that?
Don't leave me...
No choice. I've got to make things right.
By doing what?
I dunno. Whatever it takes.
C'mon sit down.
I've got palpitations. My Heart's going a hundred miles an hour. I Swear I'm going to faint.
Well you're in the right place for it. I'll get one of them young doctors to examine you shall I? Stacey'll be O.K. She's as tough as old boots, that one.
Why's Charlie taking so long?
Here he is.
She's coming round, they think she's
Oh thank God. When can we see her?
In a bit.
What did they say?
Well they said it was something calledGHB.
What's that?
Well it's a Liquid ecstasy. Nasty stuff.
Like last time.
Last time? What last time?
Well a couple of years ago someone spiked her drink.
You what? Why would someone go and do a thing like that?
Because they're evil. There's people like that everywhere you turn.
Hello sweetheart what you doing up?
Music woke me.
Oh, sorry, I didn't realise. Is Oscar awake?
Haven't heard him.
OK...
I think I'm gonna go to bed.
You do that. And Abi...
Yeah?
I Love you.
Max! Open up! Max. Get out here! Get out here! Branning.
I'm going to kill you! You hear me!! You're dead!!
Come on out you coward! C'MON!!
MAX!!
Just lie still sweetheart, no need to move...
You're in hospital.
You alright, luv. How are you feeling?
Like I've been hit by a truck.
What you been getting up to? Silly. Had us all scared.
I'm alright.
I can't believe this. It's the second time it's happened to you.
You've got to stay away from that club luv.
What you talking about?
Well someone spiked your drink.
Who said that?
We just assumed that.
---I know you, you don't do drugs and stuff.
Don't I?
Not our Stace...
Only reason ‚your Stace' went to that club was to get off
I think you should rest or something, you're all over the place, you're not making any sense...
Do you want me say it again then? what bit didn't you understand?
Oi Open up!
Let me in!
Ssh What the hell are you doing?? I've got kids asleep upstairs!
Is he here?
Who?
Who do you think!
How dare you come barging in my house like this.
Max!!
As if he's going to be round here!
Max!!
I told you he's not here!!
He ain't at Jack's he's got to be somewhere.
Where is he!?
A) I don't know and B) I don't care. Now get the hell out of my house before I call the police.
This isn't the Stacey I know...
Maybe you don't know me then mum.
I do and you don't do stuff like that.
Not drugs.
I'm not an addict, I just fancied it alright. Everything's fine now anyway, so why don't you forget about it,and move on.
But you were so happy... We all were...
Yeah,rocking mum.
You didn't need to go and do this. You could've come to me if you were feeling a bit low, we could've talked and worked things out.
My way seemed better.
You could've died.
Well I didn't, so why don't you all just back off.
Don't be like that...
Why didn't you come to us. That's what we're here for.
And what would you have done? Eh? Made me a cup of tea and put the snooker on? Would've fixed me up a treat.
Look, let's back off a bit eh, she's had a shock and she's not quite herself right now.
What we need to do is get you out of here. Get you home, get you right again. Wouldn't that be good? Eh? Back in your own bed eh. Stacey... what do you say to that?
I prefer it here.
I wish Sean was here, he'd know what to do.
There's nothing to do mum. I'm just going to lay in this bed til they tell me I can go home. No big deal.
Can I get you anything?
Another life?
I meant.... That what you want?
This one ain't doing me much good is it?
That's all what this is about? You wanting out? Of life I mean.
I didn't say that.

I'd never thought I'd see the day. You. My Stacey. Stacey Slater. Giving up. I'm the one who gives up,I'm the one who's useless, who can't cope who hides...who jumps when the doorbell goes. What would you like to do?
What?
I can help you. I can. I'll do my best. Whatever you want Stacey. Anything at all. I swear. So come on now. You're a fighter, if your dad gave you anything it was that.
Maybe it's not that I can't fight mum. Maybe it's there nothing worth fighting for.
What look at you, you're young, beautiful, you light the place up. Nobody notices me, not really, but you, you're a world beater.
Mum...
I want you out of this bed.
Think the doctors might have
I want you up and about. Now.
Mum!
I need my daughter back.
Mum I'm not very well.
Get up. Up! Now!
Get off me!! I just want to lay here alright! And nothing you can do or say is going to change that. So why don't you just go away. You're about as much use as Uncle Charlie.
I'm not going anywhere. Not without you.
Any chance of a free medical? I'll donate my body to science. They never smile do they?
These doctors. They need to loosen up. Charlie...? Charlie?
What?
Just trying to keep it light.
Stacey is right isn't she? I'm rubbish.
Don't talk daft.
Who'd come to me eh? With my track record.
It's not your fault. It's just kids being kids. It's what they do. Stace'll be alright.
I failed her, like I failed all the others.
Look, it's been a long night---
---Kat was thirteen.
You didn't know.
I didn't face up to it did I? I didn't go on a rampage searching for Zoe's father. I just shut up shop pretended it never happened.
How does anyone know what to do?
And who was there on Little Mo's wedding day, giving her away to that wife beating animal? Blessing their marriage, making a speech,and toasting the vicious swine.
It's gone now, it's over---
---look at Lynne and her little Vivvy. And as for Belinda, I'm just a joke to her. To all my girls.
Charlie---
---I bleat on and on Mo about family and respect when it's me who don't deserve any.
We could go skating.
Do me a favour.

This Sunday. There's got to be a rink somewhere. That's what we'll do, I'll sit and watch you. Used to love that. Me and your dad used to love that. Our little Queen of the ice. You used to go so fast I'd grip your dad's hand so tight, thinking any minute she's going to fall. But you never did. You just went faster and faster.
Is this going anywhere?
Yeah, well, I think so...Isn't it?
Just, give it a rest, Mum this isn't what you do.
I've got to try. So that's what we'll do yeah, we'll go skating and you can glide round and round, for as long as you like.
Round and round. In one big circle you mean? Getting absolutely nowhere.
Well...No. That's not what I meant. I just thought that you were happy then and you could be again.
By going skating?
It's not as stupid as taking drugs. You won't find any
I wasn't looking for answers.
What were you looking for then?
No idea.
Well maybe there's your problem. You won't make yourself happy again until you've decided what it is you want. I mean it's got to be out there somewhere, hasn't it?
Make it sound so easy.
It is. Once you know where to look.
I can't believe you crossed the Square on your own.
I Had to. Lauren said it was all over between you and mum.
Yeah, uh... Yeah, looks that way.
You promised me that everything would be alright.
I know I did, and I tried hard to keep that promise, I did. But I just couldn't alright. And maybe at the end of the day this is the best thing for all of us.
Not for me.
I'm sorry babe. I really am. But this is us now.
Doesn't have to be though, does it?
Thing is, right your dad, was a bit stupid. Well. Very stupid. And your mum's had enough of that. So she's got that dvd now, from Christmas, it's evidence, and it means she can hang me.
Hang you. Not really babe..Just an expression. But when we get to court I'm going to lose. Which means losing your mum. Forever. But I'll still have you. And that's something pretty special. Me and
Dad...
Okay, I think we're all happy for you to go home now.
Thanks.
But take it easy for a bit.
Easy? That's not my style.
One not five. That's what you want.
I don't want one and five.
You sort it out. Bet Stacey wished she'd never come through our door. Come and stay with us I said, I'll look after you...

Listen you old fool, you've never let me down, not once. When Viv died I had nothing. And I thought that was it for me,and what was the point anymore? You took me in? You came to my rescue? Without you Charlie there wouldn't be a Mo Harris.
See - I can't do anything right.
You were the man my little girl married. And if you was good enough for her you're good enough for me.
You can take Stacey home now...
Oh thank you so much doctor, thank you so much.
There you go. It's all coming good.
I want you to leave.
Ain't going to happen.
Why are you really here Sean?
Still deciding.
Could at least tell me the choices. Maybe I could help.
Maybe I'm here for you.
Wasted journey.
What?
I was wondering when you were going to get round to it.I mean I even drained the bottle so you wouldn't spill any. Do it.
Don't tempt me.
I won't try and stop you. Kill me.
Right, all set?
Alright precious, we're back---
Where is she?
The dvd, the one from Christmas...
Yeah?
What if mum didn't have it?
Yeah But she has, luv.
C'mon! C'mon one hit should do it right to the temple. In some cases a blow to the head is as good as a knife or a bullet. I should know.
You hit someone?
Didn't have much choice. Didn't appreciate being lied to.
That's some temper.
They tried to
Who's they?

I did a Stacey,night after night,getting off my head, as much as I could stomach... Then oned day he starts up, has a right old pop. I tried so hard to block it out. But he kept on and on and on at me. Getting louder and louder. And I just crack. and I lash out. Hard. Fast. bam! Next day he's gone. Next day he's gone forever.
Who is this Sean?
Who?
Yeah...
He was my dad. I killed my dad...
She's not in the ladies.
All her things are gone, the stuff I brought in for her, everything.
Where's that doctor? Somebody must have seen her, she couldn't have gone far.
Where is she?
Let's not panic. She's
My dad was a builder. He worked up on the scaffolding. And his friends they told me that he went all pale his legs turned to jelly and all of a sudden he fell.
Thought you just said you hit him?
It was me that caused the fall. Delayed reaction. My fault. Now every time I look in a mirror I see him. His anger...Looking back at me. Accusing me. So there it is. That's me.
Right...
Right? Is that all you can say?
Why are you telling me all this Sean?
I want you to know why I left Stacey. Why she turned out the way she has. You're the only person who would understand. You're all I want.
Don't?
What...?
You know exactly what you're doing.
What d'you mean?
Don't take me for a fool...Sean, I've heard enough lies to last me a lifetime.
I tell you the truth.
I don't believe you.
Why would I lie?
Because that's the sort of man I attract. Men who'll say anything to just get what they want from me.
That's not me.
Oh wake up Sean. You're as bad as Max.
Babe I'd better just have a quick chat with your mum.
No way. She'll kill me for being out this late.
I've been calling her.
Well don't. Cuz I'm going to sort things. Alright?
See you later.
So where am I supposed to go now?
It's not my problem.
Would you stop with that.
Just seeing if she's left a message.
It'd make a noise wouldn't it.
I know but---
---Has it made a noise? Right, so Stacey hasn't sent a message. Leave it until she does.
I think we should get some shut eye.
I can't sleep. Not til I hear from her, know she's alright.
You'll hear from her Jean. When she's good and ready.
I'm gonna stay by my phone - all night if I have to.

Line: Stace?

Scene_info: TRING RAILWAY STATION EXT DAY LIGHT
Line: Mum... Mum, just listen. Alright? Mum... Calm down... I'm fine. I've just got stuff I need to do. I'll call you after. Don't call me because I won't answer. Do you understand?
It's her, she's alright, that was Stacey, she just phoned.
Where is she?
Uh... She didn't say.
Didn't you think to ask?
She wouldn't let me get a word in. But she's safe.
Yeah. S'pose that's something.
Fancy a knees up?
Sorry?
I've got an idea we're going to have a bit of a party later.
Party?
Well you don't look well.
I'm just tired.
I'm going to nip over the minute mart, get you some cough mixture. Lauren, Lauren, can you keep an eye on Abi and Oscar for me please.
O.K.
Don't open the door to anyone will you.
I'm just nipping to the Minute Mart I won't be a minute.
You alright Abs.
Yeah.
Idiot.
Me? Watch where you're going.
As if I wasn't already in a hurry and now I've got to go and buy more cough mixture.
For who? Everything alright?
Abi. But don't worry about that.
She's still my daughter. And if she's not well I do want to know about her.
It's just a cough.
So who's looking after her?
Look Max I haven't got time for this.
Well make some time will ya. Cos if you're working I'm around today. So, if it's alright with you, I can have her round Jack's.
If you think I'm letting the girls anywhere near you---
No I will sort something out with work alright.
Maybe you should sort Abi out. Only you stand there playing the concerned mum and you don't even know your own daughter she slipped out of the house last night.
What?
She came round to see me, it was gone one o'clock.
Max, I've heard enough of your lies to last---
---Why d'you think I was calling you? You couldn't even be bothered to pick up the phone could you? No I brought her back meself.
Well she's safe and sound now, where she belongs.
I still want to see her.
Tough. Cos when you closed me out of your life, you closed them out an all.
This isn't on.
Neither was sleeping with your daughter-in-law.
Guess who's just been on the phone?
I didn't hear it ring.
Was upstairs. Well go on, ask me.
Not in the mood.
Belinda.
what'd she want?
She's coming round to dinner. Her and Neville.
Honest?
Scout's honour. Now how about you take this list - - and get yourself down the supermarket.
What's brought this on?
She just said she fancied seeing you.
Right, well uh, I'd better get moving.
You do that. Belinda. It's me. How d'you fancy a bit of lunch? No? Well let me rephrase that. Your dad needs you, so get yourself round here.
Well?
What?
What d'you think? How's Stacy?
She's alright. No thanks to you.
We going to start this again are we?
You were meant to be there for her.
Which is why I'm here now innit.
She's uh, she's in bed, sleeping, doctor said she needed peace and quiet. No visitors.
Must've been pretty bad then.
You should know.
Belinda, its your nan. Do you fancy a spot of lunch? No?! Well let me re-phrase that, you're dad needs ya, so get yerself round here!
Stacey's alright. Just let you know she's okay.
Yeah well let's hope she's learned her lesson eh.
Doubt if she'll be taking any pills ---
Sorry Sean I haven't got time.
Hang on. I just wanna say I'm sorry.
Yeah, well... Some things best forgotten in't they?
Wish I could.
You know you could always get some help, talk to someone.
They'd probably just lock me up.
You'll be alright. You got this far in't you.
And you?
Me?
You alright?
Never better.
Good. Good. But the day you're not, you know where I am.
What are you doing?
Uh nothing, uh, I didn't hear you come back.
That's not exactly answering my question Abi.
If you don't leave I'm calling the police.
You've got two choices. One you let me in. Two I stand out here, all day if I have to, and screaming my head off about our mutual friend Max. Where shall we start? his kissing technique?
Get in here!
Give it to me.
And I don't want you and dad splitting up.
And I don't want you sneaking out of the house all hours.
I just wanted to see him. I want him back here with us.
Darling. It's not going to happen alright. I don't love your dad anymore.
Yeah But you could, things could be like they were.
Sweetheart, it's not a fairy tale.
I don't want you hanging him.
You what?? In court.
He told you that did he? S'pose this was his idea.
No... Was mine. And I deleted it from the computer andLauren taped over the original one ages ago.
No no no Look at me. Look at me.
Did your dad tell you to ruin that dvd?
No!
Can't believe you'd do this to me.
And I can't believe you'd do this to him.
He's really worked on you hasn't he.
We were just talking.
I'll bet you were. I'll bet you were. Except he was doing all the chatting and you were just sitting there like a wide eyed puppy. Can see it now. Well I'm not having him using you like this.
It was my idea.
Don't protect him.
Well I've wrecked it now, so you can't hurt him!
I'm the one who got hurt Abi!
What about me and Lauren?
Abi! Come back Abi!
I'm not leaving til you tell me where he is.
Do you think it's going to be that easy?
He's still my husband.
He might not see it like that.
Let's give him the choice then shall we?
Over my dead body.
I need to see him Rachel, there's things I need him to hear.
That I seriously doubt.
You've got no right to interfere. It's between me and him. And no one else.
You're wasting your time. I don't know where he is.
He wouldn't not tell you.
You obviously don't realise how much you and Max hurt him. So why don't you chew on that while you're skulking back to Walford. He's gone Stacey. And I've no idea where.
Listen I'll just check my diary--- ---Can you just hold on...
Max! Open up! MAX!!
Can I call you back in just a sec? Alright thank you.
You have done yourself proud this time!
Yeah right And nice to see you an all.
I thought I told you to stay away from my kids!
What you mean our kids.
You really did a number on Abi last night.
As far as I know all I did was make her some hot chocolate.
And the rest.
I don't know what your problem is but why don't you stick the front door back on its hinges and leave.
You're sick.
Well, well... That what I think it is? Oh well that changes things a bit.
How could you use her like that!?
I did not get Abi to do that.
This what it's going to be like in court? Just One lie after another. I hope they do flaming hang you.
I didn't know about this. alright. What d'you think I am?
I think you know that by now.
I didn't get her to do that.
Liar!
I swear to you. On my life.
That's not exactly worth much.
Well it is to me babe. And it is to Abi. She was upset, she came round we had a cuddle...
I'm not buying it.
Well Lauren told her stuff. I just backed it up. We sat through there,we didn't say a lot...And we just held each other.
Give me a break.
Babe - that is one scared and broken little girl.
Yes well we know who's to blame for that.
Absolutely. I hold up my hands to that. But that ain't gonna help her. And she's over there now and one of us should be round there with her. Not round here having a barney.
I do not leave my kids on their own. Dot's there.
Whatever. But I've never seen my little girl in such a state. Because us being together Tan means everything to her. Everything.
So where would he go? Friends, Relatives, who?
