Yes.
Mum ...
Look. Eight O'clock. Don't be late. Please.
I love you -

Scene_info: SLATERS', LIVING ROOM INT DAY LIGHT
Line: What so that's it? You're just gonna carry on behind Max's back.

Scene_info: SLATERS', LIVING ROOM INT DAY LIGHT
Line: I wouldn't preach if I was you.

Scene_info: SLATERS', LIVING ROOM INT DAY LIGHT
Line: She doesn't love you.

Scene_info: SLATERS', LIVING ROOM INT DAY LIGHT
Line: What so she can love him but she can't love me. What am I so repulsive?

Scene_info: SLATERS', LIVING ROOM INT DAY LIGHT
Line: No, that's not what I meant...

Scene_info: SLATERS', LIVING ROOM INT DAY LIGHT
Line: She's going to leave him. She's going to take the kids, we're gonna go away.

Scene_info: SLATERS', LIVING ROOM INT DAY LIGHT
Line: What she said that?

Scene_info: SLATERS', LIVING ROOM INT DAY LIGHT
Line: It was her idea.

Scene_info: SLATERS', LIVING ROOM INT DAY LIGHT
Line: So why sneak around then? Why don't you just tell him? Why don't you just get everything out in the open?

Scene_info: SLATERS', LIVING ROOM INT DAY LIGHT
Line: Cos he deserves everything he gets.

Scene_info: SLATERS', LIVING ROOM INT DAY LIGHT
Line: What does that mean? Sean? What are these?

Scene_info: SLATERS', LIVING ROOM INT DAY LIGHT
Line: Car keys.

Scene_info: SLATERS', LIVING ROOM INT DAY LIGHT
Line: You haven't got a car.

Scene_info: SLATERS', LIVING ROOM INT DAY LIGHT
Line: Stace. I love you. You're my sister, yeah. But If I was you I'd keep my nose out of this.

Scene_info: SLATERS', LIVING ROOM INT DAY LIGHT
Line: Sean ...
That's a nice drop.
Yeah. Only the best for you..
Why don't you light a candle or something.
He's here ...
Right, are you all set then?
Can't wait. We're going.
Right then girls. You be careful. Don't go exhausting poor Bradley.
I'm pretty good actually. I used to go with Mum on Sunday mornings. Right, well I won't keep them out too late.
No, that's fine. You stay out as late as you want. It's the holidays. Take them for a burger. Go to the centre. Get some ice-creams.
Oh right.
Have fun. Enjoy yourselves.
Mum, I don't feel very well. I might stay here.
No, no, you can't. Bradley's made all this effort. You've got to go. Besides exercise will do you good, won't it. Don't you think Bradley?
Well, I mean if she doesn't feel too good -
Of course she does -
Babe if she doesn't want to go.
Of course she does. It's only a sniffle.
Mum I've got the flu.
Tanya, honestly if -
She's fine. She's fine. Go on. Don't keep Bradley waiting.
Have a nice meal.
Thank you darling.
I'm going to check on
See you later.
I'm gonna bring you back a pressie. Something for Easter.
He doesn't like chocolates.
Not chocolate. Sherbert lemons ...
Ooooh. Yes please. They're my favourite.
Right come on then you two. Last one to the bus stop has to hold my hand on the ice.
I'll hold your hand Bradley.
Bradley, I really appreciate you doing this.
I'm doing it for the girls.
You know me and Tanya saw a solicitor today. The divorce is off. If you and me could talk. Just go out for a drink, Bradley. A quick drink. It'd mean the world.
I've gotta go.
Well ... it's just the two of us. Cheers.
Steven can you take Peter's as well please?
Where's Bobby?
At Christian's.
Why did you say that about Lucy?
Are you going to tell Peter? Because if you are, I don't think I can handle that as well.
No.
She hit me. I hit her. It was a slap. It wasn't ... it was a mistake. That was it.
I know.
Do you? Do you really? Or do you think I've done something else? Something worse?
To us. It's good.
Yeah? What do you think of the lamb?
Gorgeous. Well. This is nice.
You wouldn't have rather gone out for a bite?
No. I prefer it here.
You ain't drinking?
Yeah ...
You ain't touched a drop.
I've got a bit of a headache actually.
But you're alright though are you?
Oh yeah, yeah. I'm fine.
Tell you what. You ain't gonna drink. Neither am I. We can be tee-total together.
Don't be silly.
Pour us a water will you please?
I will have a drink in a minute.
Me too.
Max. I want you to have a good night. I want this to be a special night. Go on. Have a drink enjoy yourself. If you're happy. I'm happy.
Really?
Mmm.
You know what. I don't believe you.
What?
You keep saying all the right things Tan, but I just keep getting this feeling ...
What feeling?
Like you don't mean a word.
You're just paranoid.
You think?
Yeah just a bit ...
Right so one minute you hate me, you want to drag me through the courts, you wanna take my kids away. The next. The door's open. I'm back here. I'm in your bed.
I don't think it's
You tell me.
We're working things through, ain't we.
It just don't feel the same.
What do you expect?
I expect you to be straight.
Straight?
Honest about what you feel?
I am being honest ... about what I feel?
Are you?
Will you just have another drink.
Are you?
Yes! God! What do you want from me?
I want the truth!
D'you think I'd hurt my own daughter!
I didn't say that!
Oh, don't act all innocent. I mean that's what you're getting at.. that's what you're implying
Ian. You need to get some sleep.
Aren't you? Aren't you?!
Are you gonna hit me now? Cos I'm warning you. I hit back.
I'm sorry.
So am I. Yes ... yes...yes.... right ... It's the police.
Hello ... yes speaking ... what about ... well can't you tell me now ... cos I want to know ... Right ... yes ... no, I'll come there ... Yeah, I'll come now ... They've found a body.
We met the solicitor. I signed the document. What more do you want from me,eh?
I want you.
You've got me.
Have I? I don't know. The other night, in bed, I just had this feeling like you weren't really into it.
What do you want a gold star?
What is it? What d'you want? I mean d'you want to take things slow, or what. I just...
Babe just tell me will you...just tell me what's wrong.
There's nothing wrong.
All I want to do...All I want to do is to make it up to you, alright. To be together. I don't want you to take me back. Not if you don't want to. It has to be your choice.
My choice?! What choice have you given me, eh? You haven't given me a choice about anything. You've given me no choice at all.
Are you still seeing Sean?
No ...
Well go on. You can tell me.
I'm not.
What is it - A fling -
Nothing's going on?
Pay back. A one off. I'd forgive you -
You'd forgive me?
Just tell me. Just let me in, alright. I'll do whatever you want.
Whatever I want?
Yes.
Would you die?
You what?
What the hell does that mean?
Babes ... get us a glass of water please ...
What's the matter?
I don't know. I feel a bit ... sick ... Tanya ... Oh Tanya please ...
Babe just call me a doctor.
What's happening to me?
You've been drugged.
Where are you? Right, well get in here. Now.
Just stay here, look after Peter.
What's happened?
Nothing. I'll tell you when we get back.
Dad?
I won't be long.
If you hadn't grabbed on to me. I wouldn't have fallen over.
I'm sorry. It was just a little more difficult than I remembered.
The whole night's ruined because of you.
Oh well I'm sorry, but I can't actually walk.
Stop, stop. I'll carry you.
What?
Like a princess. Right you ready?
You're so strong Bradley.
You know, Tanya's gonna kill me.
How much did you give him?
Enough. Where's the van?
Out back?
Everything else?
Done.
You okay?
We just need to ... we just need to ...
We need to get out of here. Now. Come on.
Come on then.
You're my hero Bradley.
Ian. Ian. We don't know anything yet. We don't know if it's Lucy.
Then why did the police call us?
Mummy ... you'll never believe what's happened ... Mum ...
Careful. There you go. I imagine Tanya's probably got some pain killers. You just need something to get the swelling down a bit that's all.
Someone should go in the back with him?
No. We'll both go in the front.
What if he wakes up?
He won't.
What if he does?
Just drive.
Maybe they went out for dinner.
This is dinner.
A drink then. Listen why don't we go into the front room, sit down with a nice DVD and eat loads and loads of crisps.
Brilliant. Could I choose the DVD?
Well -
Oh thanks Bradley. You're the best.
Great.
Where is it?
It's over there. Just past them trees, alright. Come on.
Mr. And Mrs. Beale?
Where is she?
Why don't we sit down for a moment.
I want to see her now.
We should sit first. Talk. You need to prepare yourself.
That's probably them now. Be careful. Alright
Is Tanya in?
It's over there ...
Come on. Give me
I know. We just ... we just need to do it ... just do it, just need to get it done, get it over with and then I'll be free. I'll be free ... won't I?
Yes. We'll be free.
He deserves it, anyway. He's brought it on himself, ain't he.
Come on.
Help me out 'ere.
Get me out ... Get me out ...
What you doing?
I'm finishing him off.
No. No ...
What?
Just leave him. Just fill it in.
Tanya. He's still alive.
I know.
How long till he wakes up?
What's he gonna do, dig himself out? Just fill it in!
You really do hate him, don't you.
What's that?
What?
That? Listen.
I don't hear anything.
Listen.
Tanya. It's nothing -
Wait. There ...
A simple yes or no will be fine.
What are you doing?
I'll be back in a second. I'm just gonna make sure they're gone.
You can't leave me here.
Just sit tight.
Sean!
Mr. Beale. Is this your daughter?
No .... No.
Where am I? What have you done to me?
It's your worst nightmare. Remember. Now you're gonna know. Now you're gonna understand just a tiny little bit of how I feel.
Every lie, every cheating worthless moment, every time you used the kids against me.
Tanya -
You'll have hours to think about what you did to me.
Please Tanya. Please don't. The kids - the kids, babe, don't - don't please. Tanya.
Goodbye Max.
Tanya please. Tanya.
They've gone ...
Hi this is the Brannings... please leave a message after the tone thank you.
That's probably your mum.
Abi, Lauren ... pick up please...
Hi Dad...
... You won't believe what's happened.
Ani...
And I've got you a present, your favourite.
Tell him about my ankle.
Abi!
He's hung up.
You probably bored him so much he fell asleep.
Oh shut up Lauren.
Girls, girls please. I'm sure he'll phone back in a bit.
I'm gonna tell him Lauren's being horrible to me.
Well you chose the DVD? I've seen this, like er, six times.
Girls.
How long do you reckon he'll last? A few hours? Five? Not that long.
I can still hear him.
Let's get out of here.
Tanya ... Tanya, there's no going back now. It's done. He's gone. It's just you and me now. Come on.
Get changed.
I didn't bring any spare clothes.
What? What you gonna do? Wander back in the square looking like that?
Yeah.
Do you realise what we just done?!
Yeah, I do -
Do you realise?
Tanya, chill out alright.
We've gotta be careful. We need to be really very careful.
Well look, we'll pull into a garage on the way back and have a wash up okay.
What if someone sees us?
Well we'll be careful. Look Tanya, just relax okay. I love you.
Sean! We have to go. Now. Do you understand. We have to go.
Alright.
Stop here. I'll walk the rest of the way. Clean out the van. Make sure no-one sees you.
You er, you sure you're alright?
Yeah.
He deserved it.
I know.
All those things he did to you.
I better go.
Tan? Tan? When am I gonna see you?
I don't know.
Tomorrow?
No, no. Not for a while.
When?
Um. I need to get home. The girls will be back soon. So we'll talk tomorrow yeah, I'll call you. Don't call me, I'll call you. Just make sure no-one sees you. Get out of them clothes. Burn them.
Tan, Tanya ...
Tanya. Oh sorry. Er, are you okay?
Yes, sorry, Um, I wasn't expecting you back yet so...
Yeah, well there was a little accident actually. Um, it's Lauren. It's her ankle, she's twisted it. Or sprained. I can never tell which is which.
It really hurts Mum.
And Abi's asleep on the sofa and Oscar's asleep upstairs.
Why you wearing that tracksuit? What happened to your hair.
What?
That tracksuit? You've changed.
Yes. Um, I know I spilt something on it. I had this in the car... It was in a terrible mess ...
Where's Dad?
He's coming later.
Later?
Yes, let's let Bradley get home shall we. You must be exhausted looking after these girls on your own.
Where did you go?
What? Out for dinner.
But dinner's on the table.
Yeah, I burnt it. Um, look, it's a long story. I'll tell you in a bit shall I?
Well thanks ever so much Bradley.
No, it's no problem. I really enjoyed myself
We'll see you soon.
Yeah. I''ll see you soon.
You and Dad have had a row. Ain't you?
Oh look you're walking on it, so it can't be too bad eh? Must be just twisted rather than sprained. Let me check it and then we'll put a pillow under it tonight and have another look in the morning.
What happened with Dad?
Nothing.
Mum, I'm not stupid. You're back and he's not.
I thought it was all sorted out. I thought that's why you went to the solicitors.
Yeah well, um, things weren't quite as simple as I thought they'd be.
What do you mean?
I don't want to talk about this right now.
Mum -
Not now alright. We'll discuss it in the morning.
Ain't he coming back tonight?
No.
Well when then?
Um... I don't...
Mum ...
Don't breathe a word. Don't say anything to Abi. Cause I don't want her worrying.
I fell asleep.
Come on, bed with you, it's late.
Where's Dad? I got him a present.
Um, he'll be back later. Come on bed. Come on..
Sean .... What you doing?
Oh um, Gus, he locked me out. I just needed to pick some stuff.
That's Uncle Charlie's.
Yeah I, er, it's raining.
What have you done Sean?
Nothing.
Is it something to do with Tanya? Or with Max? Have you done something to Max?
No.
You're lying.
Sean. I'm your sister. Whatever it is. You can tell me.
No, no I can't Stace. I don't trust you anymore. You aon't on my side.
Of course you can trust me. She's done this to you. Tanya's turned you against me.

Just stay out of my face. I kept your grubby little secret and look where it got us. Right here. Now if it's alright with you I won't take advice from you on my love life. I'm fine. I'm happy. Take a look at yourself.
Mind if I come in?
What do you want -
What do I want? I want to talk about Sean. No Max?
Um, look I can't do -
Look I know about you and Sean. He told me.
Wha ...
... what did he tell you?
About your seedy little fling. You're using him. You're using him to get at Max. I know you don't love him.
Look you don't -

Now you listen to me. You might think you know what you're dealing with but you don't. Right, Sean ain't like normal people. You can't just wind him up not expect him not to blow. Because he will. And when he does. It ain't gonna be pretty. Now Tayna please, I am asking you... I'm asking you nicely, to just leave my brother alone. It ain't gonna make you happy, it ain't gonna make the girls happy. It ain't gonna help anyone.
You don't know what you're talking about?
No? Well I think he might have done soemthing to Max. I think he might have hurt him.
That's impossible.
You don't know Sean.
Max is upstairs.
What?
He's upstairs. He's asleep. So you got it wrong.
Upstairs?
Yeah.
Now?
Yeah, he's not well. What? You don't believe me, pop up, slip into bed with him. Be like old times wouldn't it.
You gonna tell him about Sean?
I'd like you to go.
How can you be so stupid?
What right ... what right have you got to come in here and criticize me? After everything you did to me and my
Revenge is that it?
Go.
What? What are you gonna get out of it. Are you gonna hurt Max like he hurt you?
You have got no idea what has gone on between me and him.
No I don't. But I can guess. I spent five months with him. I know what makes him tick. I know how low, how sneaky he can be, but I also know that it weren't all him.
You're just a kid. Right, he took advantage.
Do I really look like a kid to you.
Yeah.
I give as good as I get. I wanted him too.
I don't want to hear this.

I asked him to leave you. I asked him again and again. I begged him. And if he had. I'd have been with him. I'd have been with him now. So it might suit you to think that it was all Max but it wasn't, not really, not in the end.
Why you telling me all this eh?
Because I don't want you using Sean to punish him, I don't want you wrecking your family cause of me. I just, I just want it all over.
It is over. It's all over. Will you please just go home now and leave me alone.
Just tell him.
Dad ....
Please... Please ... please ...
I'm sorry
You left me to die.
Why ... why ...how... why, Tanya. Why d'you come back?
Because I'm weak. Weak. I'm weak. I can't even do this properly. Well you got your way. You won.
Won?
Just like you said you would.
I Won?!

You pushed me and tricked me and cornered me till I took you back. Till I had to take you back. And for what eh? To be my husband? You're not my husband, you're my enemy. Well, you got what you wanted. Take the kids. Take your life back. 'Cause I ain't got what it takes to fight you.
You tried to kill me.
But I didn't did I? I didn't have the guts to go through with it.
Why? Why not?
I don't know. The girls ... stupid bag of sweets.
What were you gonna tell the girls?
That you'd left, that you'd gone away.
Yeah, you think that they'd believe that?
People leave all the time Max. You think they wouldn't move on?
Is that what you were gonna do? Were you gonna mocve on?

Look at me. Look at me. Look at my eyes. This is what you've done to me. You destroyed me. You've stolen my life. You've deceived me. I can't think straight cause of you. I can't have any normal feelings.
Nothing. I can't even hold my own child, my own baby boy'cause every time I do all is see is you.

I'm... I'm sick, I'm sick Max ... I need to get better, I need to... I need to recover and you won't let me... will ya? I loved you with all my heart ... and now ... even now ... there's still something there. How disgusting is that? To still have feelings like that. But not you though eh? Not you. The only person you love is yourself ... is Max Branning ... king of the world ain't he? That's what you tell yourself. I know the truth, inside you‚re just, you're just a frightened, sad, lonely little boy, frightened kid who's dad didn't love him enough. And it's all... it's all so pathetic. I just don't care any more. I don't care what happens to me. You ... you've broken me. I've got nothing left. I just... I just don't care ...
What if I went?
Why would you?

Well, 'cause I love ya... It makes me sick to see you like this... What I've done to ya... It makes me sick. All I wanted was a fresh start. I can't have that can I? Christmas time, you asked me to do the right thing and I didn't. If you meant what you said ... that you still got feelings ... if there was the slightest ... tiniest ... the slightest little hope ... that you might me... really want me... that we could be together again ... I'd go.
You don't have to do this you know. Max.
I said I'd go though. I meant it.
But the girls?
I see those girls. I talk to them. I ain't going anywhere.
You... You went back there?
He's going.
Going? I thought you wanted him dead.
So did I.
Tanya, I told you I loved you. You said... you said you loved me.
I don't.

We made plans. We made plans. You and me. The girls ... Why are you doing this to me? I won't let you do this. Tan, I won't let you do this. How would you like it if I told the girls eh? Told them about last night?
How would you like it if I told Stacey what really happened to her Dad. It's your choice Sean.
Tell those kids I love them yeah?
You really gonna do this?

Babe, only when you need me... When you... Yeah, yeah, when you want me... When your ready, you just.. er.. if you want me home Tan you just text me alright... That's all you gotta do... All you've gotta do is...er... is text me... alright... 'Come home' ... That's all alright and day or night... I'll be here... alright... I'll be here, as quick as I can... Go on, you better get inside.
I love you.
Dad? Okay ... alright, just one drink alright. But that's all. It doesn't mean anything. It's just a drink.
Thanks Bradley. Thanks mate... It means the world to me...
You alright...
Yeah, yeah, yeah. I'm fine.
Well, let me know.
